OL,7,FThe wounded man ran back to the hostel
OL,8,Fshouting 'the old man has been
OL,9,Fstabbed' and the emergency services
OL,10,Fwere called.
OL,12,FDespite their best efforts, life was
OL,13,Fpronounced extinct at 3.57pm - and a
OL,14,Fpost mortem revealed he sustained 55
OL,15,Fstab wounds including defensive
OL,16,Finjuries.
OL,18,FLenaghan, who was described in the
OL,19,Faftermath of the murder as being 'calm
OL,20,Fbut out of it' and covered in blood,
OL,21,Fwalked back to his accommodation.
OL,1,Wj5k7j5                          G6/13
